Coca-Cola Company to Relaunch Coke Zero as Coca-Cola Zero Sugar

Posted 10:01 AM, July 26, 2017, by Tribune Media Wire, Updated at 10:02AM, July 26, 2017 

Share this:FacebookTwitterGoogleLinkedInPinterestEmail 






Coca-Cola announced Wednesday the company will relaunch Coke Zero as Coca-Cola Zero Sugar in the U.S.
The new zero-calorie soda will have a red label and will have an “even better-tasting recipe.”
“It is a reinvention of Coke Zero,” new CEO James Quincey said on Wednesday’s earnings conference call. “It is part of what we call the one-brand strategy. It’s less switching between brands, which will ultimately help us keep and attract more consumers.”



Meet Coca-Cola Zero Sugar, the new and improved Coke Zero coming to the U.S. this August: https://t.co/rnMIDOS8Xj pic.twitter.com/U6s770uBna
— The Coca-Cola Co. (@CocaColaCo) July 26, 2017


As for the changing recipe? Coca-Cola says consumer testing of the new recipe was conducted for over a year.
Coke Zero first launched in 2005 as a rival to Diet Coke, which has decreased in popularity over the last 10 years.
Coke Zero Sugar is expected to launch in the U.S. in August, according to MSNBC. The soda has already been introduced in Great Britain, Mexico and 25 other markets across the globe.

















 




 


